    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="611"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24607/5.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am very grateful to you for your kind message of sympathy in the irreparable
                    loss which my country has sustained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward Grey.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
